
[1]destitute

   DESTITUTE, a. [L. To set. Literally, set from or away.]

   1. Not having or possessing; wanting; as destitute of virtue, or of
   peity; destitute of food and clothing. It differs from deprived, as it
   does not necessarily imply previous possession.

   2. Needy; abject; comfortless; friendless.

   He will regard the prayer of the destitute. Ps. 102.

            DESTITUTE, n. One who is without friends or comfort.

                               DESTITUTE, v.t.

   1. To forsake.

   2. To deprive.
